$r = random(2,8,1);
$theta = random(100,125,1); #stay away from zeros of sine/cosine


$ans1 = Compute("$r^2(cos(2*$theta)+i*sin(2*$theta))");

$ans2 = $r**2*cos(2*$theta);
$ans3 = $r**2*sin(2*$theta);


###########################
#  Main text

BEGIN_PGML
Find [`z^2`] in polar form and rectangular form where [`z=[$r](\cos([$theta]^\circ)+i\sin([$theta]^\circ))`]. 

Polar form is [` r(\cos(\theta)+i\sin(\theta)) `], with [` r>0, 0^\circ \leq \theta \leq 360^\circ`].


Polar form: [`z^2=`] [______________________________]{$ans1} [@ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") @]*

Rectangular form: [`z^2=`] [____]{$ans2}+[____]{$ans3}[`i`]     


END_PGML


